##Three shifts for makers of coronavirus test kits: 100,000 people a day is the limit | prism

Micro-signal Lengjing

Feature Introduction, tencent news product column, "Prism" focus on financial in-depth reports.

By Xiaochuan Jiang
Production | prism tencent Xiaoman studio

Welcome to download tencent news APP for more quality information

Manufacturers of Ministry of Health of the People's Republic of China's designated nucleic acid test kits are working overtime to meet the evolving needs of the epidemic. A National Health Commission designated Procurement Enterprise Employees told the "prism, " at present, "the company's own employees back to the company, not home for the New Year

Nucleic acid kits are used for the detection of COVID-19(2019-nCoV) but do not involve treatment. Earlier reports said the lack of local detection kits in Hubei, more than patients infected with pneumonia can not be confirmed.

In the National Health Commission to the underground on the confirmation of COVID-19 pneumonia procedure, it is clear that the provincial CDC Shanghai Huirui, Shanghai Geno and Shanghai Bojie three companies to purchase nucleic acid test kits.

The kit developer, who asked not to be named, said the current "three shifts throughout the company, 100,000 people a day production is already the limit. "

Three reagent box manufacturers are in the external delivery

Shanghai based Berger said in a statement that it had prepared new coronavirus related nucleic acid detection reagents for 2019, as well as semi automatic and fully automatic extractors and other products. Local media in Shanghai reported that Berger was already shipping to users outside the city.

State-owned Assets Supervision and Administration Commission News Center "state-owned Assets Xiaoxin" said, shanghai Geno, a subsidiary of Sinopharm's China biosciences, "was the first to successfully develop a COVID-19 nucleic acid molecular detection kit and sent it to the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention for verification... the Kit has been supplied to most provinces of the country, including Hong Kong and Macau. ".

Shanghai Huirui staff said that the current advisory nucleic acid kit procurement units, too many to cope. The company launched the Middle East Respiratory Syndrome coronavirus test kit in 2015 in conjunction with the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention.

Research and development success to the market or green approval

Nucleic acid kits belong to medical devices, the market must be approved by the Department of Drug Control. "The 'R & D Success' mentioned in the announcements of many listed companies does not mean it can be listed, " senior medical investors told prism. "In case of an emergency, we can go through the Green Channel for approval and apply for product registration. "

Previously, listed companies including peabody, BGI, Xilong biology and Kehua biology have all said they have successfully developed a nucleic acid test kit for COVID-19, some of the company's statement to the provincial CDC supply.

The State Food and Drug Administration said on January 22 that it would prepare for emergency review and approval of drugs and medical devices needed for epidemic prevention and control "at any time in accordance with the requirements of laws, regulations and work requirements. "

In one case from Guangdong, medical device supplier Ozida said its client Guangzhou Anjie used to prevent respiratory droplets and air-borne diseases in isolation of the medical bed "hard fight for three days and two nights. " Has Been approved by the FDA. This is the first conditional rapid approval case made by the Guangdong Provincial Drug Administration with reference to the "emergency approval procedure for medical devices" .

Chen Huawei, a partner at Fuhai Oriental, a venture capital firm, speculates that one of the reasons for the current difficulties in scaling up production capacity of nucleic acid kits is the lack of production staff during the Spring Festival holiday, which has also made it difficult to procure raw materials due to the progress of the epidemic.

The confirmation procedure will be completed within 24 hours after the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention or a third-party testing organization, called BGI, receives the test samples, the NMHC said in its confirmation procedure.

A testing agency staff told prism that the third-party testing agency mainly provides testing services, through quality process control, to ensure the accuracy of test results of kits. The implication is that the kit test may have inaccurate results.

The theory is that the nucleic acid test kit is mature and well-defined, which is why the development is so fast, say researchers familiar with the development of the reagent. However, it should be noted that there are false-negative and false-positive detection of the situation, it is possible to consume more kits to do repeated testing.
